Package: CNVmap
Title: An R-package to visualize Copy Number Variations (CNVs)
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Brando", "Poggiali", email= "poggialibrando1995@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: 'CNVmap' is a tool for visualizing Copy Number Varitions (CNVs) at genome, chromosome and gene levels.
             It can be use to inspect CNVs and create pubblication-quality figures. The inputs of this tool are .cns and .cnr file
             formats obtained by the tool CNVkit (https://cnvkit.readthedocs.io/en/stable/).
License: MIT LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10),
    BiocGenerics,
    IRanges (>= 2.30.1),
    GenomicRanges (>= 1.48.0),
    GenomeInfoDb,
    ggplot2,
    plyranges
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    data.table
